# Copy to .env locally (never commit real secrets).
# Vite variables must be prefixed with VITE_

# ── Supabase (browser-safe keys only) ──
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co
# VITE_SUPABASE_PROJECT_ID=YOUR_PROJECT_REF
# VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=your_anon_public_key

# ── X / Twitter API (server-side only — DO NOT use VITE_ for bearer tokens) ──
#
# Lovable: Project → Secrets → Add new secret (same Name as below). Save, then redeploy/publish
# so Edge Functions pick up the new env vars.
#
# Configure on Supabase CLI (if not using Lovable secrets UI):
#   supabase secrets set TWITTER_BEARER_TOKEN=your_bearer_token
# Optional alias:
#   supabase secrets set X_BEARER_TOKEN=your_bearer_token
#
# Recent Search v2 uses Bearer (app-only) auth. Consumer API key + secret are for OAuth 1.0a
# user-context flows; this app’s social-intel function does not read them unless you add that later.
#
# Same bearer is used by: social-intel (per industry) + data-collector (broad macro/market tweets).
# LinkedIn is not scraped (ToS/API); use official LinkedIn APIs if you add that integration.

# ── pg_cron → Edge Functions (NOT in .env) ──
# Scheduled data-collector + auto-intel use Postgres app setting:
#   app.supabase_service_role_jwt = <service_role JWT>
# Set via SQL on the database (see docs/cron-scheduling.md). Do not put service_role in the frontend.
